article.headline: Grambling 75, Jackson State 65
article.story: GRAMBLING, La. (AP) -- Paul Haynes had 19 points, six rebounds and three assists to lead Grambling State to a 75-65 win over Jackson State on Saturday night. Ron Ellis posted a double-double with 10 points and 10 rebounds while handing out five assists for Grambling (9-15, 7-7 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Brion Rush had 16 points, six rebounds and Anthony Williams came off the bench to score 10 points. He also had three rebounds and two steals. Jackson State (10-13, 8-6) was led by Ishmael Joyce who had a game-high 25 points making 8-of-18 field goals. He also grabbed nine rebounds, had seven steals and four assists. Ernest Hassell added 12 connecting on 6-of-7 shots from the floor. Grambling led 40-20 at halftime.
